reviewText: LOVE IT!! what a TRIPPY movie set>> so bad it's good :)
Good Saturday entertainment. They are separate episodes.
Maybe corny maybe camp, but a Saturday afternoon when it is raining or snowing this can fill the day without you looking out the window. Smile or laugh, feel, be happy with enjoyment.

Republic Studio's televesion version suffers from the absense of its' "Serial-Drums of Fu Manchu" star, Henry Brandon.  Given his excellent portrayal, it's stunning the studio failed to capitalize on its success. Nonetheless, it contains all the episodes that were filmed.
